 from the link: 
sensitive label can "Protect containers that include Teams, Microsoft 365 Groups, and SharePoint sites. For example, set privacy settings, external user access and external sharing, and access from unmanaged devices."

Given answers are correct according to link. For the first part;
Although you can restrict access to users in your own organization, you can also extend access to any other user who has an account in Azure Active Directory (Azure AD). If external users don't have an account in Azure AD, they can authenticate by using guest accounts in your tenant.

"For example, with the encryption settings for a sensitivity label, you can protect content so that: The current price list that is sent to business partners can't be opened after a specified date."
